{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a0c03183-fc06-409e-83f2-b465e6f6b46f","content":"### How it works\n\nWith trusted publishing, **no API key is needed**. The `dotnet nuget push` command automatically picks up the OIDC token when:\n\n1. The `id-token: write` permission is set\n2. The workflow/repo/environment match what's registered on nuget.org\n3. No `--api-key` is passed (NuGet falls back to OIDC)\n\n### To publish a release:\n\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\n### Also recommended:\n\n- Create a GitHub **environment** called `nuget` (Settings → Environments) to add protection rules like required reviewers.\n- Set `<Version>` in your `.csproj` or use `/p:Version=$(git describe --tags)` in the pack step.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dad05970-cdc6-4fc1-89a8-9ca9e2e51f4a","outputTokens":193,"requestId":"1431:DE6C9:134D0E7:1595946:6A027A61"},"id":"ed67d4c5-694a-4415-a499-d35e2469fcb8","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:55:06.427Z","parentId":"2eb0bf68-3187-43ce-bcdf-ddff9f3a9ca6"}
